Science Learning Center  n        The Science Learning Center  SLC  room     in the Science n        and Engineering South building  SES  is a place in which n        all levels of expertise meet and exchange ideas  It is home n        to the sciences  biology  chemistry  earth and n        environmental science and physics  Students can obtain n        tutoring in many of the     level science courses from n        graduate teaching assistants who keep regular office hours n        each week as well as from student tutors who have recently n        excelled in those classes  Students may also find their n        teacher in the Center as many of them use the open  n        friendly spaces available in the center for their office n        hours  The Center is a great place to meet friends to go n        over homework problems and to study for exams  The Science n        Learning Center also contains computers for general use as n        well as a formal computer lab that is overseen by the n        Academic Computing and Communications Center  ACCC  and an n        ACCC consultant is available to assist computer users at n        all times  In addition  inside the Science Learning Center n        is a UIC office of WISE  the Women in Science and n        Engineering Program  n         Dr  Clark and the staff at the SLC are committed to providing a welcoming environment to all students   In accordance with the University of Illinois non discrimination  policy  we are committed to the most fundamental principles of academic  freedom  equality of opportunity  and human dignity    All decisions are based on individual merit and are free from invidious discrimination in all its forms   We will not engage in discrimination or harassment against any person because of race  color  religion  national origin  ancestry  age  marital status  disability  sexual orientation including gender identity  unfavorable discharge from the military or status as a protected veteran and will comply with all federal and state nondiscrimination  equal opportunity and affirmative action laws  orders and regulations   Dr  Clark is a participant in the Safe Zone program at UIC that creates and supports allies for the lesbian  gay  bisexual  transgender  queer and questioning communities  n n        The Science Learning Center is also home to peer led study n        groups that focus on the sciences  Student leaders  who are n        trained in group dynamics and problem solving techniques  n        have expertise in a particular subject area  Generally the n        peer  Peer leaders n        guide their students toward development of sound study n        skills by encouraging them to work together to solve n        problems  In this manner students contribute to the n        solution of a problem even as they learn techniques and n        skills from their peers  The goal of the peer led study n        groups is to assist students to develop individual study n        strategies tailored to the demands of a specific n        discipline  n         n nHOURS  n              AM        PM  Monday through Thursday    AM    PM Friday      n        The SLC is closed evenings  weekends and school holidays  n         n n        TA office hours and professor office hours are scheduled at n        the start of each semester  although a request to reserve a n        time in one of the study areas may be made at any time n        during the semester for open times rooms  The SLC may also n        be used for departmental activities such as holiday n        parties  All queries regarding the use of the SLC should be n        directed to Dr  Clark  see bottom of page for an email n        link  except for queries regarding scheduling of the n        computer lab inside the SLC   these should be directed to n        the ACCC  n n Safe Zone  Ginevra Clark Contact Me n n     CDATA  nvar  rwObsfuscatedHref    "mai" var  rwObsfuscatedHref    "lto" var  rwObsfuscatedHref    " ml